bug.short_desc: IE10 Mouse Event getDocumentLeft() returns a value of type float.

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1279 Screenshot of IE10 web console
Hi there,
I added a screenshot of a bug that occurs with IE10. The tooltip doesn't open at the correct position (it opens at 0,0) and the application breaks. Because anywhere in the layout stack the return value of getDocumentLeft() is checked if it's an integer.
I tested on two devices with the same browser update version, diffrent results of pageX. Maybe it's another mouse driver?
My fix is: parseInt(this._native.pageX, 10) https://github.com/qooxdoo/qooxdoo/blob/master/framework/source/class/qx/event/type/Mouse.js#L227
The same issue in getDocumentTop() function.
I hope you could fix it also in the 2.x release.
Thanks, Timo

Thanks for the report. The float values are returned from the native event and represent the values the browser generates. I guess the difference on the systems is the dpi scaling setting of windows itself. At least that was the reason we found when we had the same problem in the framework. But returning these values is the right thing to do here because we don't know if someone needs that accuracy in a custom app. So parsing those values to int's is not a good idea in my opinion. The other option is to parse the values before positioning the tooltip. I guess that fix would be in your code, right?
Yes, that's right. I was so fixed to the position at the mouse event, because of the return type in the JSDoc above.
